import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["rate"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["rate"].median():.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the overall distribution of unemployment rates?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='rate', ascending=False)
    top_10 = data.head(10)
    plt.bar(top_10['id'], top_10['rate'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=top_10['rate'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Maximum rate: {top_10["rate"].max():.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('Location ID')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('Which location has the highest unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_unemployment_rate = data.groupby('id')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_unemployment_rate['id'], avg_unemployment_rate['rate'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=avg_unemployment_rate['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    ax.set_xlabel('Location ID')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the average unemployment rate by location?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['id'] = pd.to_datetime(data['id'], format='%Y%m%d')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['id'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['id'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of unemployment rates over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
